Citation.sAbstract: Densities and surface tensions for the binary mixtures of 1,2,4-trimethylbenzene and 1,3,5-trimethylbenzene  with isopropyl acetate and isobutyl acetate have been measured over the whole composition range. The  measurements were made under normal atmospheric pressure and at the temperatures (298.15, 308.15, and  313.15) K. The excess molar volumes and surface tension deviations are derived from the experimental  data. The excess molar volumes for all the binary systems are positive, and the surface tension deviations  are negative.
Citation.sTitle: Excess Molar Volumes and Surface Tensions of 1,2,4-Trimethylbenzene and 1,3,5-Trimethylbenzene with Isopropyl Acetate and Isobutyl Acetate at (298.15, 308.15, and 313.15) K
